### A rhythm that keeps strict time: the metronome pattern

```scheme
;; Metronome click on every quarter beat, 4/4, no variation
(transport/tempo 100)
(define (click beat)
  (note/place-at beat 'C5 'sixteenth 0.5))

(click 1)
(click 2)
(click 3)
(click 4)
(click 5)
(click 6)
(click 7)
(click 8)
```

`[VISUAL: Two measures in 4/4. A single sixteenth-note click on each quarter beat. No variation in velocity or timing — perfectly even.]`

<!-- BUILD: render metronome staff; each note-sprite bops in perfect synchrony -->

---


### A two-bar ostinato with rests

```scheme
;; Repeating two-measure rhythmic figure
(transport/tempo 108)
(define (ostinato-bar start)
  (note/place-at start 'E3 'eighth 0.8)
  (note/place-at (+ start 0.5) 'E3 'eighth 0.8)
  ;; rest at beat 2
  (note/place-at (+ start 2) 'A3 'eighth 0.85)
  (note/place-at (+ start 3) 'E3 'quarter 0.75))

(ostinato-bar 1)
(ostinato-bar 5)
(ostinato-bar 9)
```

`[VISUAL: Three identical two-measure units. Each has: eighth-eighth-rest-eighth-quarter. The pattern loops.]`

<!-- BUILD: render repeating ostinato staff with rest glyphs -->

