### Crescendo over a steady rhythm

```scheme
;; Four measures, same rhythm, velocity increasing
(transport/tempo 100)
(note/place-at 1 'C4 'quarter 0.4)
(note/place-at 2 'D4 'quarter 0.4)
(note/place-at 3 'E4 'quarter 0.4)
(note/place-at 4 'F4 'quarter 0.4)

(note/place-at 5 'C4 'quarter 0.55)
(note/place-at 6 'D4 'quarter 0.55)
(note/place-at 7 'E4 'quarter 0.55)
(note/place-at 8 'F4 'quarter 0.55)

(note/place-at 9 'C4 'quarter 0.7)
(note/place-at 10 'D4 'quarter 0.7)
(note/place-at 11 'E4 'quarter 0.7)
(note/place-at 12 'F4 'quarter 0.7)

(note/place-at 13 'C4 'quarter 0.9)
(note/place-at 14 'D4 'quarter 0.9)
(note/place-at 15 'E4 'quarter 0.9)
(note/place-at 16 'F4 'quarter 0.9)
```

`[VISUAL: Four measures in 4/4. Same rhythm (four quarter notes per measure). A crescendo hairpin (<) spanning all four measures, with dynamic markings p → mf → f → ff.]`

