### A phrase with fermata (held note)

A fermata tells the performer to hold a note longer than its written duration. The engine does not yet support fermatas as notation *[needs: GAP-2]*, but you can manually extend the duration.

```scheme
;; A phrase ending with a held note
(transport/tempo 100)
(note/place-at 1 'G4 'quarter 0.8)
(note/place-at 2 'A4 'quarter 0.8)
(note/place-at 3 'B4 'quarter 0.8)
(note/place-at 4 'C5 'whole 0.85)  ;; held longer than the measure *[needs: GAP-2]*
```

`[VISUAL: Three quarter notes, then a whole note with a fermata symbol (𝄐) above it.]`

<!-- BUILD: when GAP-2 fermata glyph is added, render it above the final note; note-sprite holds its animation longer -->

---


### A 6/8 compound meter (two beats, each divided into three)

In `6/8`, there are two *felt* beats per measure, each subdivided into three eighth notes.

```scheme
;; A 6/8 phrase
(transport/tempo 120)
(note/place-at 1 'D4 'eighth 0.8)
(note/place-at 1.5 'E4 'eighth 0.7)
(note/place-at 2 'F4 'eighth 0.7)

(note/place-at 2.5 'G4 'eighth 0.8)
(note/place-at 3 'F4 'eighth 0.7)
(note/place-at 3.5 'E4 'eighth 0.7)
```

`[VISUAL: One measure in 6/8 time. Six eighth notes, grouped into two beats (three notes each). Beaming shows the 3+3 division.]`

<!-- BUILD: render 6/8 time signature; beaming groups three eighths per beat -->

---


### Accent patterns: shifting the strong beat

```scheme
;; Four measures, accent on a different beat each time
(transport/tempo 110)
;; measure 1: accent beat 1
(note/place-at 1 'C4 'quarter 0.9)
(note/place-at 2 'C4 'quarter 0.6)
(note/place-at 3 'C4 'quarter 0.6)
(note/place-at 4 'C4 'quarter 0.6)

;; measure 2: accent beat 2
(note/place-at 5 'C4 'quarter 0.6)
(note/place-at 6 'C4 'quarter 0.9)
(note/place-at 7 'C4 'quarter 0.6)
(note/place-at 8 'C4 'quarter 0.6)

;; measure 3: accent beat 3
(note/place-at 9 'C4 'quarter 0.6)
(note/place-at 10 'C4 'quarter 0.6)
(note/place-at 11 'C4 'quarter 0.9)
(note/place-at 12 'C4 'quarter 0.6)

;; measure 4: accent beat 4
