### A rhythm with grace notes

Grace notes are ornamental, very short notes that \"steal\" time from the main note. They are not yet in the engine *[needs: GAP-2]*, but you can approximate them with very short durations.

```scheme
;; Approximating grace notes with sixteenths
(transport/tempo 100)
(note/place-at 1 'B3 'sixteenth 0.6)     ;; grace note
(note/place-at 1.25 'C4 'quarter 0.85)   ;; main note (slightly delayed)
(note/place-at 2.25 'D4 'quarter 0.8)
```

*[needs: GAP-2]* — true grace-note glyphs and timing are not yet supported.

`[VISUAL: A small sixteenth note (B3) with a slash through the stem (grace note notation), immediately before a quarter note (C4).]`

<!-- BUILD: when GAP-2 grace-note glyph is added, render slashed note-head; grace note-sprite is tiny, fast -->

