### A phrase with a half-note triplet

Half-note triplets (three half notes in the time of two) are rare but striking. *[needs: GAP-1]*

```scheme
;; Three half notes over two measures (4/4 each = 8 beats total)
;; Each half-note triplet lasts 8/3 = 2.667 beats
(transport/tempo 80)
(note/place-at 1 'C4 'half 0.8)          ;; triplet half *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/place-at 3.667 'E4 'half 0.8)
(note/place-at 6.333 'G4 'half 0.8)
```

