### A rhythm that subdivides unevenly (Scotch snap)

A Scotch snap is a short note on the beat followed by a longer note — the reverse of the usual long-short pattern.

```scheme
;; Scotch snap: short-long
(transport/tempo 100)
(note/place-at 1 'D4 'sixteenth 0.85)
(note/place-at 1.25 'D4 'eighth 0.75)   ;; dotted would be better *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/place-at 1.75 'E4 'sixteenth 0.85)
(note/place-at 2 'E4 'eighth 0.75)
```

`[VISUAL: Staff showing the short-long Scotch snap pattern. A sixteenth immediately followed by a dotted eighth (when GAP-1 closes).]`

<!-- BUILD: when dotted eighths are added, render the Scotch snap accurately -->

