### A 9/8 meter (three beats, each divided into three)

`9/8` is a compound triple meter: three beats per measure, each subdivided into three eighth notes.

```scheme
;; A 9/8 phrase
(transport/tempo 120)
(note/place-at 1 'G4 'eighth 0.8)
(note/place-at 1.5 'A4 'eighth 0.7)
(note/place-at 2 'B4 'eighth 0.7)

(note/place-at 2.5 'C5 'eighth 0.8)
(note/place-at 3 'B4 'eighth 0.7)
(note/place-at 3.5 'A4 'eighth 0.7)

(note/place-at 4 'G4 'eighth 0.8)
(note/place-at 4.5 'F4 'eighth 0.7)
(note/place-at 5 'E4 'eighth 0.7)
```

