### Mixing durations within a measure

A measure can hold any combination of durations, as long as the total equals the measure's beat count.

In 4/4, you can have:
- Four quarter notes (1+1+1+1 = 4)
- Two half notes (2+2 = 4)
- One whole note (4 = 4)
- One half, two quarters (2+1+1 = 4)
- Eight eighth notes (0.5+0.5+0.5+0.5+0.5+0.5+0.5+0.5 = 4)

```scheme
;; A 4/4 measure with mixed durations: half, quarter, quarter
(transport/tempo 100)
(note/strike 60 'half 64)
(note/strike 64 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 67 'quarter 64)
```

The half note lasts two beats, then two quarter notes (one beat each) finish the measure.

`[VISUAL: A 4/4 measure with a half note on C, then two quarter notes on E and G.]`

<!-- BUILD: render a 4/4 measure: half note, then two quarter notes -->

---


### Eighth notes: subdividing the beat

An **eighth note** lasts half a beat. Two eighth notes fit in the space of one quarter note.

```scheme
;; A measure of eight eighth notes in 4/4
(transport/tempo 100)
(note/strike 60 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 62 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 65 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 67 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 65 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 62 'eighth 64)
```

Eight eighth notes = four beats. The measure is full.

`[VISUAL: A 4/4 measure with eight eighth notes ascending and descending the C major scale.]`

<!-- BUILD: render a 4/4 measure with eight beamed eighth notes -->

---


### A march with eighth-note runs

Marches often use eighth notes for filler or flourish.

```scheme
;; A 2/4 march measure with a quarter note and two eighths
(transport/tempo 120)
(note/strike 60 'quarter 80)
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 62 'eighth 64)
```

The quarter note fills one beat, the two eighths fill the second beat.

`[VISUAL: A 2/4 measure: one quarter note, two beamed eighth notes.]`

<!-- BUILD: render a 2/4 measure with one quarter note and two beamed eighth notes -->

Here is a four-measure march that uses this pattern:

```scheme
;; A four-measure 2/4 march with eighth-note pickups
(transport/tempo 120)

;; Measure 1
(note/strike 60 'quarter 80)
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 62 'eighth 64)

;; Measure 2
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 60 'quarter 80)
(note/strike 65 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)

;; Measure 3
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 67 'quarter 80)
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 65 'eighth 64)

;; Measure 4
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 60 'quarter 80)
(note/strike 60 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 60 'eighth 64)
```

`[VISUAL: Four measures of 2/4, each with one quarter note and two eighth notes.]`

