### A steady bass drum on the downbeat

Rhythm is not only melody. Let us use the `beat` form to place a bass drum on every downbeat.

```scheme
;; A four-measure 4/4 pattern with bass drum on every downbeat
(transport/tempo 100)

(define (downbeat-kick measure-count)
  (if (> measure-count 0)
      (begin
        (beat \"x...\") ;; kick on beat 1, rests on 2, 3, 4
        (downbeat-kick (- measure-count 1)))
      '()))

(downbeat-kick 4)
```

Each measure has four beats. The `beat` form `\"x...\"` means \"sound on beat 1, rest on beats 2, 3, 4.\" The function repeats this four times.

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures. A bass drum notation symbol appears on beat 1 of each measure.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures with a bass drum glyph on beat 1 of each -->

---


### Layering rhythm: kick and snare

A drum pattern typically has multiple instruments. Let us add a snare on beats 2 and 4.

```scheme
;; A four-measure 4/4 drum pattern: kick on 1 and 3, snare on 2 and 4
(transport/tempo 100)

(define (kick-snare-pattern measure-count)
  (if (> measure-count 0)
      (begin
        (beat \"x.o.\") ;; x=kick (1,3), o=snare (2,4)
        (kick-snare-pattern (- measure-count 1)))
      '()))

(kick-snare-pattern 4)
```

`\"x.o.\"` means: kick on beat 1, snare on beat 2, kick on beat 3, snare on beat 4. That is the fundamental backbeat.

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures. Bass drum on beats 1 and 3, snare drum on beats 2 and 4.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures with kick glyphs on beats 1 and 3, snare glyphs on beats 2 and 4 -->

---


### A march drum pattern

A march emphasizes the downbeat strongly and often doubles the bass drum.

```scheme
;; A 2/4 march drum pattern
(transport/tempo 120)

(define (march-drum measures)
  (if (> measures 0)
      (begin
        (beat \"xo\") ;; kick on beat 1, snare on beat 2
        (march-drum (- measures 1)))
      '()))

(march-drum 8)
```

Eight measures of 2/4, each with kick on 1, snare on 2. Strong-weak, strong-weak. A march.

`[VISUAL: Eight 2/4 measures. Kick on beat 1, snare on beat 2, repeated.]`

<!-- BUILD: render eight 2/4 measures with kick on 1, snare on 2 -->

