### Combining melody and rhythm

Let us place a melody on top of a drum pattern.

```scheme
;; A four-measure 4/4 pattern: melody + backbeat
(transport/tempo 100)

;; Drum pattern
(define (backbeat)
  (beat \"x.o.\"))

;; Melody for one measure
(define (melody-measure pitch)
  (note/strike pitch 'quarter 64)
  (note/strike (+ pitch 2) 'quarter 64)
  (note/strike (+ pitch 4) 'quarter 64)
  (note/strike (+ pitch 5) 'quarter 64))

;; Four measures, layered
(backbeat)
(melody-measure 60)

(base/land-on-downbeat)
(backbeat)
(melody-measure 62)

(base/land-on-downbeat)
(backbeat)
(melody-measure 64)

(base/land-on-downbeat)
(backbeat)
(melody-measure 65)
```

Each measure has a drum pattern (`backbeat`) and a melody that ascends by step. The drums and melody sound simultaneously.

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures on two staves. Top staff: melody ascending in quarter notes. Bottom staff: kick and snare pattern.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures on two staves, top with melody, bottom with kick/snare drum pattern -->

