### Dotted rhythms: uneven subdivision

A **dotted note** is 1.5 times its normal duration. A dotted quarter note lasts 1.5 beats (one quarter + one eighth). A dotted eighth lasts 0.75 beats (one eighth + one sixteenth).

Dotted rhythms are common in marches and fanfares — they create a *long-short* pattern.

```scheme
;; A 4/4 measure with dotted quarter notes
(transport/tempo 100)
(note/strike 60 'quarter 80) ;; dotted quarter (1.5 beats) *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/strike 62 'eighth 64)  ;; eighth (0.5 beats)
(note/strike 64 'quarter 80) ;; dotted quarter (1.5 beats) *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/strike 65 'eighth 64)  ;; eighth (0.5 beats)
```

This measure has two dotted-quarter + eighth pairs. The rhythm is: LONG-short, LONG-short.

`[VISUAL: A 4/4 measure with two dotted-quarter notes, each followed by an eighth note.]`

<!-- BUILD: render a 4/4 measure with two dotted-quarter + eighth pairs (awaits GAP-1: dotted duration support) -->

Dotted durations are GAP-1. When GAP-1 closes, you will be able to write `'dotted-quarter` and `'dotted-eighth` directly.

---


### A fanfare rhythm in 4/4

Fanfares often use dotted rhythms to create a regal, punctuated feel.

```scheme
;; A four-measure fanfare in 4/4 with dotted rhythms *[needs: GAP-1]*
(transport/tempo 120)

;; Measure 1
(note/strike 60 'quarter 80)  ;; dotted quarter *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 67 'quarter 80)  ;; dotted quarter *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/strike 64 'eighth 64)

;; Measure 2
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 60 'half 80)

;; Measure 3
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 65 'quarter 80)  ;; dotted quarter *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/strike 69 'eighth 64)
(note/strike 72 'quarter 80)  ;; dotted quarter *[needs: GAP-1]*
(note/strike 69 'eighth 64)

;; Measure 4
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 60 'whole 80)
```

Measures 1 and 3 use the dotted-quarter + eighth pattern. Measure 2 is a half note. Measure 4 is a whole note (four beats).

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures. Measures 1 and 3 have dotted rhythms. Measure 2 has a half note. Measure 4 has a whole note.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures with dotted rhythms in measures 1 and 3, half note in measure 2, whole note in measure 4 (awaits GAP-1) -->

