### A rhythmic ostinato

An **ostinato** is a repeated rhythmic or melodic pattern. Let us write a bass ostinato that repeats every measure.

```scheme
;; A four-measure bass ostinato in 4/4
(transport/tempo 100)

(define (bass-ostinato pitch)
  (note/strike pitch 'quarter 72)
  (note/strike pitch 'eighth 64)
  (note/strike pitch 'eighth 64)
  (note/strike pitch 'quarter 72)
  (note/strike pitch 'quarter 64))

;; Repeat the ostinato four times
(bass-ostinato 48)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(bass-ostinato 48)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(bass-ostinato 48)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(bass-ostinato 48)
```

The pattern is: quarter, eighth, eighth, quarter, quarter. It repeats on the same pitch (low C, MIDI 48) for four measures.

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures on a bass staff, all showing the same rhythmic pattern on low C.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures on bass staff with repeated ostinato pattern -->

---


### Layering ostinato and melody

An ostinato can serve as a foundation for a melody.

```scheme
;; A four-measure pattern: ostinato + melody
(transport/tempo 100)

(define (bass-ostinato pitch)
  (note/strike pitch 'quarter 72)
  (note/strike pitch 'eighth 64)
  (note/strike pitch 'eighth 64)
  (note/strike pitch 'quarter 72)
  (note/strike pitch 'quarter 64))

(define (melody-line pitches)
  (if (not (null? pitches))
      (begin
        (note/strike (car pitches) 'quarter 64)
        (melody-line (cdr pitches)))
      '()))

;; Measure 1
(bass-ostinato 48)
(melody-line '(60 62 64 65))

;; Measure 2
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(bass-ostinato 48)
(melody-line '(67 65 64 62))

;; Measure 3
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(bass-ostinato 48)
(melody-line '(60 64 67 72))

;; Measure 4
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(bass-ostinato 48)
(melody-line '(60))
(note/strike 60 'half 72) ;; end on a long note
```

The bass repeats the same pattern. The melody changes each measure. In measure 4, the melody ends early and holds a half note.

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures on two staves. Bottom staff: repeated ostinato. Top staff: changing melody.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures on two staves, bottom with ostinato, top with melody -->

