### A polymeter: 3/4 over 4/4

**Polymeter** is when two time signatures are used simultaneously. One voice plays in 3/4, another in 4/4.

This is advanced, and the transport currently handles one global tempo and one implied meter per voice. But you can *approximate* polymeter by carefully placing notes at fractional beats.

```scheme
;; A two-measure polymeter: one voice in 3/4, one in 4/4
(transport/tempo 120)

;; Voice 1: 3/4 (measures of 3 beats)
(define (voice-3/4)
  (note/strike 60 'quarter 64)
  (note/strike 64 'quarter 64)
  (note/strike 67 'quarter 64))

;; Voice 2: 4/4 (measures of 4 beats)
(define (voice-4/4)
  (note/strike 48 'quarter 72)
  (note/strike 48 'quarter 64)
  (note/strike 48 'quarter 64)
  (note/strike 48 'quarter 64))

;; Simultaneously play both patterns
(voice-3/4)
(voice-4/4)

;; After 3 beats, voice-3/4 repeats; after 4 beats, voice-4/4 repeats
;; To continue, you'd need to manually align or use a looping construct
```

The two voices are out of phase. Voice 1 repeats every 3 beats, voice 2 every 4 beats. They realign after 12 beats (the least common multiple).

`[VISUAL: Two staves over the same time span. Top staff in 3/4 time signature, bottom in 4/4, with barlines that do not align.]`

<!-- BUILD: render two staves with different time signatures over the same time span, barlines offset -->

Polymeter is at the edge of what the current transport can handle cleanly — this is a taste, not a full implementation.

---


### A shuffle rhythm: swung eighths

A **shuffle** is when pairs of eighth notes are played unevenly: the first eighth is longer, the second shorter, creating a triplet feel even though they are notated as straight eighths. This is \"swing.\"

The engine does not yet have a swing/shuffle mode (GAP-1), but you can approximate it using triplets or by manually adjusting note placements.

```scheme
;; A shuffle rhythm approximated with manual beat placement
(transport/tempo 100)

;; Instead of even eighths (0.5 + 0.5 = 1 beat),
;; we place the first note at beat 0, the second at beat 0.66 (2/3 of a beat)
(base/at-beat 0 (note/strike 60 'eighth 64))
(base/at-beat 0.66 (note/strike 62 'eighth 64))

(base/at-beat 1 (note/strike 64 'eighth 64))
(base/at-beat 1.66 (note/strike 65 'eighth 64))

(base/at-beat 2 (note/strike 67 'eighth 64))
(base/at-beat 2.66 (note/strike 65 'eighth 64))

(base/at-beat 3 (note/strike 64 'eighth 64))
(base/at-beat 3.66 (note/strike 62 'eighth 64))
```

Each pair of notes has a long-short (2:1) ratio, like a triplet. This creates the shuffle feel.

`[VISUAL: A 4/4 measure with pairs of eighth notes, but the spacing is uneven — first note of each pair is longer.]`

<!-- BUILD: render a 4/4 measure with pairs of eighth notes spaced to show shuffle timing -->

When GAP-1 closes, you will be able to mark a passage or piece as \"swing\" and the engine will apply the shuffle automatically.

---


### A clave pattern (3-2 son clave)

The **clave** is a rhythmic foundation in Afro-Cuban music. The **3-2 son clave** is a five-note pattern spread over two measures of 4/4.

Measure 1 has three notes (the \"three\" side). Measure 2 has two notes (the \"two\" side).

```scheme
;; A 3-2 son clave pattern
(transport/tempo 100)

;; Measure 1: three notes
(base/at-beat 0 (sfx \"woodblock\"))     ;; beat 1
(base/at-beat 1.5 (sfx \"woodblock\"))   ;; and of 2
(base/at-beat 3 (sfx \"woodblock\"))     ;; beat 4

;; Measure 2: two notes
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(base/at-beat 1 (sfx \"woodblock\"))     ;; beat 2
(base/at-beat 2.5 (sfx \"woodblock\"))   ;; and of 3
```

The clave is asymmetric. It locks the rhythm in place.

`[VISUAL: Two 4/4 measures. Measure 1 has percussion hits on beats 1, 1.5, and 3. Measure 2 has hits on beats 1 and 2.5.]`

<!-- BUILD: render two 4/4 measures with percussion notation showing clave pattern -->

---


### Layering clave with a bassline

The clave provides the grid. Let us add a bassline on top.

```scheme
;; A two-measure clave + bass pattern
(transport/tempo 100)

;; Clave measure 1
(base/at-beat 0 (sfx \"woodblock\"))
(base/at-beat 1.5 (sfx \"woodblock\"))
(base/at-beat 3 (sfx \"woodblock\"))

;; Bass measure 1
(base/at-beat 0 (note/strike 48 'quarter 72))
(base/at-beat 2 (note/strike 48 'eighth 64))
(base/at-beat 2.5 (note/strike 50 'eighth 64))
(base/at-beat 3 (note/strike 52 'quarter 64))

;; Clave measure 2
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(base/at-beat 1 (sfx \"woodblock\"))
(base/at-beat 2.5 (sfx \"woodblock\"))

;; Bass measure 2
(base/at-beat 0 (note/strike 48 'half 72))
(base/at-beat 2 (note/strike 53 'quarter 64))
(base/at-beat 3 (note/strike 52 'quarter 64))
```

The clave clicks in the background. The bass moves around it, landing on and off the clave accents.

`[VISUAL: Two 4/4 measures on two staves. Top staff: woodblock clave pattern. Bottom staff: bass notes.]`

<!-- BUILD: render two 4/4 measures on two staves, top with clave, bottom with bass -->

