### A two-measure loop with drums and bass

Let us combine kick, snare, and bass into a repeating two-measure groove.

```scheme
;; A two-measure groove: drums + bass
(transport/tempo 110)

(define (two-bar-groove)
  ;; Measure 1
  (beat \"x.o.x.o.\")  ;; kick on 1 and 3, snare on 2 and 4
  (base/at-beat 0 (note/strike 48 'quarter 72))
  (base/at-beat 1 (note/strike 50 'eighth 64))
  (base/at-beat 1.5 (note/strike 48 'eighth 64))
  (base/at-beat 2 (note/strike 52 'quarter 64))
  (base/at-beat 3 (note/strike 53 'quarter 64))

  ;; Measure 2
  (base/land-on-downbeat)
  (beat \"x.o.x.o.\")
  (base/at-beat 0 (note/strike 48 'quarter 72))
  (base/at-beat 1.5 (note/strike 50 'eighth 80))
  (base/at-beat 2 (note/strike 48 'quarter 64))
  (base/at-beat 3 (note/strike 55 'quarter 64)))

;; Play the groove twice
(two-bar-groove)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(two-bar-groove)
```

The groove repeats. The kick and snare stay constant. The bass varies slightly between measures.

`[VISUAL: Two sets of two 4/4 measures on two staves. Top: bass. Bottom: kick and snare pattern.]`

<!-- BUILD: render two iterations of a two-bar groove on two staves -->

