### Quantizing: snapping notes to the grid

When you place notes manually, you might want them to \"snap\" to the nearest beat or subdivision. This is **quantization**.

The transport does not have an automatic quantize function yet, but you can quantize by rounding your beat values.

```scheme
;; A helper to quantize a beat value to the nearest eighth note
(define (quantize-to-eighth beat)
  (* (round (* beat 2)) 0.5))

;; Place notes at approximate beats, then quantize
(transport/tempo 100)
(base/at-beat (quantize-to-eighth 0.1) (note/strike 60 'eighth 64))   ;; snaps to 0
(base/at-beat (quantize-to-eighth 0.7) (note/strike 62 'eighth 64))   ;; snaps to 0.5
(base/at-beat (quantize-to-eighth 1.3) (note/strike 64 'eighth 64))   ;; snaps to 1.5
(base/at-beat (quantize-to-eighth 2.2) (note/strike 65 'eighth 64))   ;; snaps to 2
```

Each beat value is rounded to the nearest 0.5 (eighth note). Messy input becomes a clean grid.

`[VISUAL: A 4/4 measure with four eighth notes, all aligned to exact eighth-note positions on the grid.]`

<!-- BUILD: render a 4/4 measure with eighth notes quantized to the grid -->

