### A four-on-the-floor beat

**Four-on-the-floor** is a dance-music staple: a kick drum on every beat.

```scheme
;; A four-measure four-on-the-floor pattern
(transport/tempo 120)

(define (four-on-floor)
  (beat \"xxxx\"))  ;; kick on every beat

(four-on-floor)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(four-on-floor)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(four-on-floor)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(four-on-floor)
```

Four measures, each with a kick on beats 1, 2, 3, and 4. Relentless and driving.

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures. Kick drum notation on every beat.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures with kick drum on every beat -->

---


### Adding hi-hats to the four-on-the-floor

A hi-hat on every eighth note creates a steady pulse.

```scheme
;; A four-on-the-floor pattern with hi-hats on every eighth
(transport/tempo 120)

(define (four-on-floor-with-hats)
  (beat \"xxxx\")               ;; kicks
  (beat \"hhhhhhhh\"))          ;; hi-hats on every eighth (8 per measure)

(four-on-floor-with-hats)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(four-on-floor-with-hats)
```

Two measures. Kicks on every beat, hi-hats on every eighth. This is the backbone of house music.

`[VISUAL: Two 4/4 measures on two staves. Top: hi-hats on every eighth. Bottom: kicks on every beat.]`

<!-- BUILD: render two 4/4 measures on two staves, top with hi-hats, bottom with kicks -->

