### A breakbeat: syncopated kick and snare

A **breakbeat** is a sampled or programmed drum pattern with syncopation and variation. Let us write one.

```scheme
;; A two-measure breakbeat
(transport/tempo 100)

;; Measure 1
(base/at-beat 0 (sfx \"kick\"))
(base/at-beat 0.5 (sfx \"hihat\"))
(base/at-beat 1 (sfx \"snare\"))
(base/at-beat 1.5 (sfx \"hihat\"))
(base/at-beat 2 (sfx \"kick\"))
(base/at-beat 2.75 (sfx \"kick\"))  ;; extra kick
(base/at-beat 3 (sfx \"snare\"))
(base/at-beat 3.5 (sfx \"hihat\"))

;; Measure 2
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(base/at-beat 0 (sfx \"kick\"))
(base/at-beat 0.5 (sfx \"hihat\"))
(base/at-beat 1 (sfx \"snare\"))
(base/at-beat 1.5 (sfx \"hihat\"))
(base/at-beat 2 (sfx \"kick\"))
(base/at-beat 2.5 (sfx \"hihat\"))
(base/at-beat 3 (sfx \"snare\"))
(base/at-beat 3.25 (sfx \"snare\"))  ;; extra snare
(base/at-beat 3.5 (sfx \"hihat\"))
```

The pattern has kicks, snares, and hi-hats. Measure 1 has an extra kick at beat 2.75. Measure 2 has an extra snare at beat 3.25. The syncopation gives it bounce.

`[VISUAL: Two 4/4 measures on a drum staff, with kicks, snares, and hi-hats placed at various on-beat and off-beat positions.]`

<!-- BUILD: render two 4/4 measures on drum staff with breakbeat notation -->

