### A steady metronome click

A metronome is the simplest rhythm: one click per beat.

```scheme
;; A metronome click for eight beats
(transport/tempo 100)

(define (metronome-click beats-remaining)
  (if (> beats-remaining 0)
      (begin
        (sfx \"click\")
        (base/at-beat 1 (metronome-click (- beats-remaining 1))))
      '()))

(metronome-click 8)
```

Eight beats, one click per beat. This is the grid made audible.

`[VISUAL: Eight beats on a staff, each marked with a small metronome icon.]`

<!-- BUILD: render eight beats on a staff with metronome click notation -->

