### A tempo change mid-phrase

Sometimes a phrase needs to slow down or speed up partway through. Let us change tempo after two measures.

```scheme
;; A four-measure phrase with a tempo change
(transport/tempo 100)

;; Measures 1-2 at 100 BPM
(note/strike 60 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 62 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 64 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 65 'quarter 64)

(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 67 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 65 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 64 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 62 'quarter 64)

;; Measures 3-4 at 80 BPM (slower)
(base/land-on-downbeat)
(transport/tempo 80)
(note/strike 60 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 62 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 64 'quarter 64)
(note/strike 65 'quarter 64)

(base/land-on-downbeat)
(note/strike 60 'half 72)
```

The first two measures are at 100 BPM. After the second measure, the tempo drops to 80 BPM. The final measure is slower and ends with a held note.

`[VISUAL: Four 4/4 measures. Tempo marking \"♩=100\" above measures 1-2, \"♩=80\" above measures 3-4.]`

<!-- BUILD: render four 4/4 measures with tempo change marked -->

